        <div class="col-xs-10 col-sm-6 col-md-6 col-lg-6">
          <p>Graphic designer since 2007, and Community manager since 2014, I had the chance throughout these years of experience to work in various fields (IT, health care, music, video games or tattoo).<br>

          While I really enjoy working by myself, nothing gives me more pleasure than be part of a team.<br>
          Creative and autonomous, I believe teamwork and getting connected with other people allows me to use my skills to their maximum and to learn more.</p>

          <h2>2007.</h2>
          <p>Freshly graduated from 'EAP Info-Seine in Paris', I joined my first advertising agency which will take me into the wonderful world of graphic design: models, catalogs, visual identity and so on, all this makes me want to learn more!


          <h2>2010.</h2>
          <p>Beginning of my adventure as a freelancer. In addition to DTP and visual identities, I had the opportunity to work for great agencies like 'Publicis Live', 'Lever de Rideau', or 'CCM Benchmark'.<br>
          I discover illustration and site content, which will lead me to my next passion: THE WEB.</p>


          <h2>2014.</h2>
          <p>My passion for the web and communication grew, and I decided to take Community manager training at 'Doranco' training center.<br>

          A great adventure in Parisian communication agencies like 'CCM Benchmark' and 'Spöka' will follow!</p>


          <h2>2020.</h2>
          <p>My adventures lead me to Montreal, to 'La Maison du Violon', renowned french luthier in Montreal and Laval.<br>

          In the cards: improvement of the brand image, marketing plan, redesign of the graphic charter, optimization of the content and SEO of the site, communication on social networks, press and digital advertising, newsletters…<br>

          At the same time, I start working as a freelancer, with a real thirst for new, stimulating and varied challenges.</p>


          <h2>2022.</h2>
          <p>my past experiences in communication and Marketing given the taste for challenges around the customer experience on the web.Then, I wanted to understand the mechanisms of web applications and participate directly in meeting the associated technical challenges..<br>

          After spent 1 month at 42 school learning Shell and the C language, I decided to continue on this path and change careers by learning the exciting job of web developer.<br>

          I decided to join le Wagon and ti do the 9-week full-time intensive coding bootcamp learning HTML, CSS, Bootstrap,<br>
          JavaScript ES6, SQL, git, GitHub, Heroku and Ruby on Rails.

          And now, what's next?</p>


          <h2>AND BESIDES THAT ?</h2>
          <p>Besides that, I'm passionate about entomology, tattooing, architecture and diving.<br>

          I also love electronic music (I'll be happy to share my Spotify playlist with you).<br>

          I am also a travel enthusiast. Recently returned from a year and a half in Montreal, I intend to travel the globe as many times as possible.<br>

          To learn more about my career, you can consult my <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/christelle-bettoni/">LinkedIn profile</a>.<br>

          Please feel free to drop me an <a href="#contact-me">email</a> if you have any questions.</p>
